I am trying to use Robonaut’s Coral AI model on Roboflow. However, I am having trouble understanding how to download the model from the website in the rknn format that Photon Vision expects. Some help on how that process works would be appreciated.
Also why has no one just posted the rknn file for an orange pi? seems like that would have been done already but it hasn’t.

It’s a strangely esoteric process, which requires a lot of setup and special installs to sort out, and mostly requires a linux system to be even remotely effective. Bug your programming mentors at practice, we can help run you through it. We haven’t built 118’s model, but we have built Frogforce’s.

The actual results when we tested it were pretty mixed; It’d work most of the time, but with relatively high false positive rates, and could miss coral of particular alignments.
